parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle dies while in motion
the vehicle dies at a stop
the vehicle will not restart
the engine shuts off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the flywheel can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The flywheel breaks or fails
the engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle will not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the harmonic balancer can cause the loss of power steering and accessories powered by the belt, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The harmonic balancer outer ring pulley separates from the pulley
loss of power steering
loss of accessories powered by the belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to engine stalling, difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The transmission valve fails
the transmission cannot be restarted
the vehicle drifts backward while in park
the shift indicator is difficult to see in daytime.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter solenoid can cause the engine to stall and shut off, making it difficult or impossible to restart, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls and shuts off while bringing the vehicle to a stop
the vehicle cannot be restarted
a faulty solenoid in the torque converter housing is suspected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt buckle can lead to a failure of the restraint system, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle falls apart
no longer latches
or deteriorates slowly
making it inoperable.
